    dc:creator "Nieves-Aldrey, José Luis" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Description of Fumariphilus Nieves-Aldrey, gen. nov., a new genus of herb gall wasps, with a key to genera of the tribe Aulacideini (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683374>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683376>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683380>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683378>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683384>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683390>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683392>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683388> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683374>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Portion of the phylogeny related to herb gall wasps, modified from Fig. 3 in Ronquist et al. (2015). This analysis was based on a combined molecular data set of three genes Numbers on branches indicate posterior clade probabilities (in % units) ± Monte Carlo error (errors less than 1% not shown) across four separate analyses. Only groups with a posterior probability above 70% are shown. The red box indicates the monophyletic clade containing the two species with an incorrect genus identification, evidence that supports the erection of the new genus Fumariphilus to accommodate them. The red arrows point to the phylogenetic positions of the species correctly assigned to Aylax Hartig and Neaylax Nieves-Aldrey." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683374/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683376>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, anterior view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Antenna. (D) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Mesosoma, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683376/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683380>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, dorsal view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Head, anterior view. (E) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Antenna." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683380/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683378>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Pronotum, antero-dorsal view. (B) Propodeum. (C) Mouth parts, posterior view. (D) Metatarsal claw. (E) Metasoma, lateral view. (F) Metasoma, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683378/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683384>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus, forewing and terminal instar larvae of Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb. (A), (C), (E) and Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb. (B), (D) and (F). All in lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683390>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb., SEM photos of a terminal instar larva. (A) Body, ventral view. (B) Body, lateral view. (C) Head, anterior view. (D) Detail of mouth parts. (E) Left mandible. (F) Right mandible." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683390/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683392>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb., SEM photos of a terminal instar larva. (A) Body, ventral view. (B) Body, lateral view. (C) Head, anterior view. (D) Detail of mouth parts. (E) Right mandible. (F) Left mandible." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683392/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683388>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Galls of Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb on Fumaria officinalis (A, B). (C) Section of a galled fruit showing a larva. (D) Section of a mature fruit with a fully developed adult inside. (E) Galls of Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb. on Hypecoum procumbens. (F) Section of a mature fruit with a fully developed adult inside." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6683388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

